rComments: Great instructor! Made lectures fun with in-class simulations of game theory scenarios, and gave a rigorous, insightful introduction to the math behind game theory. His test questions are not too bad if you understand math (which you really should if you are going into economics).).

DO NOT TAKE THIS COURSE WITH THIS PROF. Many students drop eco204 and take eco206 instead in the summer but his test questions are very difficult. Only take this course during Fall - Winter session. Avoid him at all costs.

Lectures have way too much math in them to be easily understandable by the vast majority of students. Teach according to the pre-requisites...
